===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{uncountable}} Metal formed into a thin, even thread, now usually by being drawn through a hole in a steel die.
# A piece of such material; a [[thread]] or slender rod of [[metal]], a [[cable]]
# A metal conductor that carries electricity.
# A [[fence]] made of usually [[barbed]] wire.
# {{sports}} A finish line of a racetrack.
# {{informal}} A [[telecommunication]] wire or cable; hence, an [[electric]] [[telegraph]]; a [[telegram]]
# {{slang}} A hidden listening device on the person of an [[undercover]] operative for the purposes of obtaining incriminating spoken evidence.
# {{informal}} A deadline or critical endpoint.
#: ''This election is going to go right to the '''wire'''''
# {{billiards}} A wire strung with [[bead]]s and hung horizontally above or near the table which is used to keep score.

